01:40:02.335 --> 01:40:04.361
They didn't know
what it was exactly,

01:40:04.439 --> 01:40:06.669
but they knew they
were going again.

01:40:06.741 --> 01:40:09.232
They hired me
because I was a diver,

01:40:09.309 --> 01:40:12.541
because I was the kind of person
that Tork needed.

01:40:12.614 --> 01:40:14.514
I met him, he trusted me.

01:40:14.582 --> 01:40:16.279
He arranged for me to
move into the building

01:40:16.352 --> 01:40:17.978
to keep an eye on the boy.

01:40:18.052 --> 01:40:19.883
I didn't even know that he was sick.

01:40:19.955 --> 01:40:21.422
You never loved him!

01:40:21.490 --> 01:40:23.048
Of course I loved him!

01:40:23.124 --> 01:40:24.592
I just wanted to protect him,

01:40:24.660 --> 01:40:28.152
and for a while,
I thought that I could.

01:40:28.230 --> 01:40:29.289
Listen to me.

01:40:29.367 --> 01:40:30.765
Listen.

01:40:30.833 --> 01:40:34.668
There's not a night
that goes by...

01:40:35.874 --> 01:40:39.468
that I don't dream
that I catch him.

01:40:41.813 --> 01:40:43.905
I catch him in my arms...

01:40:45.517 --> 01:40:48.885
...before he hits the ground.

01:41:07.741 --> 01:41:10.539
We can start over.

01:41:25.394 --> 01:41:26.953
Tork and Loyen are desperate.

01:41:27.029 --> 01:41:28.291
They're under extreme pressure.

01:41:28.364 --> 01:41:29.626
They'll show no mercy.

01:41:29.700 --> 01:41:31.633
You can hide in my cabin,

01:41:31.702 --> 01:41:33.136
but only for a little while.

01:41:33.203 --> 01:41:35.137
The ship is approaching the coast.

01:41:35.205 --> 01:41:36.828
You've to get ashore.

01:41:55.616 --> 01:41:58.551
Just go inland. Wait for me.

01:41:58.619 --> 01:42:00.746
There's a village just inside the bay

01:42:00.820 --> 01:42:02.813
about 7 miles to the south.

01:45:58.819 --> 01:46:02.812
You see how it's drawing energy

01:46:02.890 --> 01:46:05.688
from some sort of vacuum in the center?

01:46:33.356 --> 01:46:36.292
I knew you'd come.

01:46:36.361 --> 01:46:37.726
For people with resources,

01:46:37.795 --> 01:46:39.854
the right events happen.

01:46:39.932 --> 01:46:41.559
They may look like coincidences,

01:46:41.633 --> 01:46:44.500
but they arise out of necessity.

01:46:44.570 --> 01:46:45.901
Incredible, isn't it?

01:46:45.971 --> 01:46:47.438
We can see inside it.

01:46:47.506 --> 01:46:48.734
It's not a real meteorite.

01:46:48.807 --> 01:46:51.173
Meteorites are cold. This is warm.

01:46:51.243 --> 01:46:55.704
Meteorites are dead.
This... is alive.

01:46:55.783 --> 01:46:59.240
And why are you doing all this, Tork?

01:46:59.320 --> 01:47:01.413
Why, money.

01:47:01.488 --> 01:47:04.013
Fame. More money.

01:47:04.090 --> 01:47:07.424
This is the biggest scientific discovery

01:47:07.496 --> 01:47:09.156
of the century.

01:47:09.230 --> 01:47:10.663
You can't remove it and transport it

01:47:10.732 --> 01:47:12.792
to a densely populated
part of the world.

01:47:12.868 --> 01:47:15.201
Not until you know
exactly what it is.

01:47:15.270 --> 01:47:17.934
You could set off a catastrophe.

01:47:18.007 --> 01:47:19.531
Oh, death is always a waste,

01:47:19.608 --> 01:47:21.941
but sometimes it is the only way

01:47:22.012 --> 01:47:23.444
to arouse people.

01:47:23.513 --> 01:47:25.447
Bohr participated in the construction

01:47:25.515 --> 01:47:26.949
of the atom bomb

01:47:27.017 --> 01:47:28.451
and thought it would promote peace.

01:47:28.519 --> 01:47:30.453
You lack imagination, Smilla,

01:47:30.521 --> 01:47:33.957
which is unforgivable in a scientist.

01:47:34.024 --> 01:47:35.889
What about the boy?

01:47:46.971 --> 01:47:50.931
He jumped into the damn water.

01:47:51.010 --> 01:47:54.538
We were forced to take him
along into the cave.

01:47:54.615 --> 01:47:56.046
His father collapsed

01:47:56.116 --> 01:47:58.108
while he was still near the surface.

01:47:58.186 --> 01:48:00.416
The boy wanted to go to him.

01:48:00.487 --> 01:48:05.425
It was Loyen's idea
to keep him under observation.

01:48:05.493 --> 01:48:08.725
The worm was not
in his internal organs.

01:48:08.797 --> 01:48:10.423
He never even felt it.

01:48:36.962 --> 01:48:38.725
Aaarrrgh!

01:48:45.371 --> 01:48:47.396
He killed my son.

01:49:58.837 --> 01:50:00.362
Tork!

01:51:16.425 --> 01:51:17.448
Tork!

01:51:39.816 --> 01:51:42.376
The boy, Tork.

01:51:42.453 --> 01:51:44.944
Tell me about the day he died.

01:51:50.027 --> 01:51:52.461
You were waiting outside his school,

01:51:52.531 --> 01:51:53.964
weren't you, Tork?

01:51:54.032 --> 01:51:56.466
He's the only child
who walks home alone.

01:52:03.176 --> 01:52:05.838
Smilla: You follow him.

01:52:05.912 --> 01:52:09.643
You grab him,

01:52:09.717 --> 01:52:12.948
not by his arms,
but by his clothes

01:52:13.021 --> 01:52:15.989
so you don't leave any marks.

01:52:18.058 --> 01:52:20.186
But you miscalculate.

01:52:27.570 --> 01:52:29.936
He knows you, Tork,

01:52:30.005 --> 01:52:31.438
Not from the hospital

01:52:31.507 --> 01:52:33.998
where you spent hours
tormenting him,

01:52:34.076 --> 01:52:37.240
but from the day
he saw his father die.

01:52:37.313 --> 01:52:39.942
It's death itself
he associates with you.

01:52:40.017 --> 01:52:41.245
You're guessing.

01:52:45.522 --> 01:52:47.353
He gets to his building

01:52:47.425 --> 01:52:49.450
and then there's no escape.

01:52:51.530 --> 01:52:54.896
He knows what's behind him.

01:52:54.966 --> 01:52:57.765
He knows he's going to die.

01:52:57.837 --> 01:53:02.205
This fear is even stronger
than his fear of heights.

01:53:02.275 --> 01:53:04.140
Inside him an engine is spinning

01:53:04.210 --> 01:53:05.838
that will keep turning

01:53:05.911 --> 01:53:08.278
until all his strength is used up.

01:53:11.551 --> 01:53:14.487
And you chase him up to the roof.

01:53:14.555 --> 01:53:17.490
Maybe for the first time
it occurs to you

01:53:17.559 --> 01:53:19.492
not just to get the tape...

01:53:19.560 --> 01:53:22.996
but that it's possible to eliminate him.

01:53:28.070 --> 01:53:30.539
And avoid him ever telling anyone

01:53:30.605 --> 01:53:32.505
what he saw in a cave
on a glacier somewhere

01:53:32.575 --> 01:53:33.769
in the Davis Strait.

01:53:37.312 --> 01:53:38.974
I didn't mean to kill him.

01:53:39.048 --> 01:53:41.380
I needed the tape.

01:53:41.452 --> 01:53:43.648
He panicked, I shouted,

01:53:43.720 --> 01:53:46.053
he turned around, he didn't see me.

01:53:46.123 --> 01:53:48.456
You're lying.

01:53:52.030 --> 01:53:53.861
He didn't turn around.

01:53:57.034 --> 01:53:59.630
He couldn't hear a thing.

01:54:02.541 --> 01:54:04.806
He was deaf.

